description:
In rust/lichen-oscore/src/lib.rs:165-179, a manual Debug impl was added that redacts secrets:

    impl core::fmt::Debug for Context {
        fn fmt(&self, f: &mut core::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> core::fmt::Result {
            f.debug_struct('Context')
                .field('master_secret', &'[REDACTED]')
                // ...

While the Debug output is safe, the Context struct still derives Clone and its fields are accessible. If Debug is used in error messages or logs at different code paths based on field values, timing side channels could still exist.

Location: rust/lichen-oscore/src/lib.rs:165-179
Risk: Low - primarily a defense-in-depth concern.
Fix: Consider making secret fields private and only accessible through methods that take appropriate care.
